bck0083: Clean rewrite of SeqColim interface (was: CNF/DNF in bck0082)

Previous work.agda (bck0082, 1490 lines) contained the CNF/DNF + NFinCofin
normal form development. That is preserved in bck0082-work.agda.

New work.agda (115 lines, 0 holes, COMPILES) is a clean sequential colimit
interface based on OvertlyDiscrete/SeqColim.agda, reorganized:

1. Inductive ≤E ordering (_≤E_ : ℕ → ℕ → Type)
   - ≤E-refl, ≤E-step constructors
   - suc-≤E-suc, ≤E-sucʳ, ≤E-trans
   - Conversions: ≤E→≤, ≤→≤E
   - ≤→≤E-suc: ≤→≤E commutes with ≤-suc (refl on concrete pairs)
   - ≤E-retract + isProp≤E (via retract of isProp≤)

2. SeqColimMaps module (parametric over any Sequence):
   - ι : n ≤E m → X n → X m (by pattern matching: refl ↦ id, step ↦ f ∘ ι)
   - ι≤ : library ≤ version (via ≤→≤E)
   - ι-propIrrel: proof-irrelevance of ι
   - ι-comp: ι q ∘ ι p ≡ ι (≤E-trans p q)
   - ι-incl: incl x ≡ incl (ι p x) — THE KEY LEMMA, clean induction
   - ι≤-incl: library ≤ version
   - ι-pres: preservation (equal at k → equal at l ≥ k)

Key improvements over the original:
- ι-incl proved cleanly (original was stuck with holes)
- ≤E used throughout (no subst X needed, unlike ιnm)
- isProp≤E properly proven (retract method)
- Modular: SeqColimMaps works for any Sequence, not just finite ones
